<item>
            <title>[SPARK-2494] Hash of None is different cross machines in CPython</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-2494</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The hash of None, also tuple with None in it, is different cross machines, so the result will be wrong if None appear in the key of partitionBy().&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should use an portable hash function as the default partition function, which generate same hash for all the builtin immutable types, especially tuple.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;CPython 2.x &lt;/p&gt;</environment>
